Another CTF problem completed.
It was a forensic ctf problem. it's description was like this : The SOC team discovered a suspiciously large log file after a recent breach. When they opened it, they found an enormous block of encoded text instead of typical logs. Could there be something hidden within? Your mission is to inspect the resulting file and reveal the real purpose of it. The team is relying on your skills to uncover any concealed information within this unusual log.
Download the encoded data here: Logs Data. Be prepared—the file is large, and examining it thoroughly is crucial.

When I downloaded the log file, I saw that it was all just base64 dump so I opened Kali linux and ran "base64 -d" this perticular command on the given log file.
It gave me a image file in .png format, when I opened it I saw another string in the bottom of the image, Then I used chatgpt to check which format was the given string was in, it was in hexadecimal.
I ran 'echo "7069636F4354467B..." | xxd -r -p' on the whole string and got the whole flag. 
'7069636F4354467B' this is some part of the flag that I found in this CTF.
Another one completed!!
